The following year, Daley competed at the 2012 Summer Olympics and won the bronze medal.
"I knew it was what I had been dreaming of all my life, to fight in the diving at the Olympic Games in my country, there was no better feeling," he said.
This also inspired the selection of his first song, Heather Small's Proud, which refreshed him as he prepared for the Olympics and still causes him to shudder.
